	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_35352544"><p> <i>
"To clarify - is this deletion occurring because the drive analyzed the filesystem metadata and decided it would be a good idea to zero some sectors, or is it an asynchronous response to a fast TRIM command applied to an extent covering the whole drive?"</i>
</p><p>
It's not TRIM. We used a non-TRIM OS and a write blocker for this reason. The manufacturer has mentioned a garbage collector that works with NTFS, and the only way it could work is by zero-ing areas of the SSD using information gleaned from the metadata. Hope this clarifies the situation for you!<nobr> <wbr></nobr>:-)
</p><p>
Graeme.</p></div>
	</div>

