	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_35352414"><p>You're off by so many orders of magnitude, it hurts.</p><p>The chance of generating that particular e-mail, if it's 2 KiB, is 1 in 2^16384. (That's not really the number you want -- you want the chance of generating a similarly-incriminating e-mail. They're roughly equally improbable, though.)</p><p>So that's 1 in 2^16384 compared to 2^30 copies of the e-mail that would fit on the drive.</p><p>If the prosecution scoured every drive ever made for a random sequence of bits that looked like that e-mail, they'd never find it.</p><p>Plus,<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_35352414">

