	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_35349584"><p>To be honest, most data recovery from a hard drive is foiled by a simple zero anyway.  All this "must wipe several times with certain patterns" thing is cobblers.  Yes, if I was the military, I'd be doing it too, just to make sure, but no-one has yet provided convincing proof that "magnetic history" from drives can actually be recovered in anywhere near a cost-effective or reliable way.</p><p>Digital forensics consists of taking an image of the drive and seeing what you can get from that.  Any half-decent implemen<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
