	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_35349862"><p>I think it's about impoliteness when asking favors. Friends help each other: I'm quite ok fixing my non-technical friend's WLAN, just as he's ok with giving me a hand when I'm moving houses. That's the social norm, and thus asking someone for a favor also indicates how you feel about them.</p><p>So if you don't like someone, if you would under normal circumstances not want to spend time with them - then you don't ask them for favors. That would be plain rude.</p><p>If you don't have an actual friend to provide tech services - just purchase said services.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_35349862">
<span class="ind"></span><a class="btn link" href="//hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=2017726&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;cid=35349618" onclick="return D2.selectParent(35349618)">Parent</a> <div class="comment_share"> 
