		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_35349460" name="comment_link_35349460" href="//hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=2017726&amp;cid=35349460" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(35349460)" >Re:Why can't they make up their minds</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_35349460" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 35349460); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>5</a>, Insightful)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~DrgnDancer">DrgnDancer <span class="uid">(137700)</span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_35349460">		
		on Tuesday March 01 2011, @01:25PM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=2017726&amp;cid=35349460">#35349460</a>)
		<small><a href="http://www.feyknight.com/" title="http://www.feyknight.com/" class="user_homepage_display">Homepage</a> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_35349460"><p>It's not hard really.  The drives autoclean themselves.  So when you delete the inode reference to a given data file, it will be completely much more quickly that on a normal magnetic drive (which won't reclaim the space till it's needed).  On the other hand it won't respond to commands that would FORCE a magnetic drive to completely wipe the file.</p><p>So if you're in your secret lab and you hear that the evil enemy is an hour away, you just type "rm<nobr> <wbr></nobr>/*" and wander off to escape.  By the time they get there all your data will be completely wiped.  On the other hand if they are breaking down the door to your secret lab and you have only seconds left you can't type "shred<nobr> <wbr></nobr>/home/joeari/secretfile" and expect it to be perma-deleted like you could with a magnetic drive.</p><p>They recover deleted sectors more quickly, but can't be forced to do so in a controlled manner.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_35349460">
<span class="ind"></span><a class="btn link" href="//hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=2017726&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;cid=35349202" onclick="return D2.selectParent(35349202)">Parent</a> <div class="comment_share"> 
